### App Config

- Single source of truth lives in [`src/config/app.ts`](mdc:src/config/app.ts):
  - `appConfig.app` for name, description, keywords, base URL, locale, authors, categories
  - `appConfig.branding` for default OG image and social handles
  - `appConfig.theme` for colors
  - `getCanonicalUrl(path)` for building absolute URLs

### Environment

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL` should be set without a trailing slash; it is normalized in config.
- Fallback base URL is `http://localhost:3000` for local dev.

### Layout Metadata

- Top-level `src/app/layout.tsx` should use:
  - `metadataBase: new URL(appConfig.app.baseUrl)`
  - `alternates.canonical: appConfig.app.baseUrl`
  - Derive `title`, `description`, and Open Graph from `appConfig`.

### Metadata Routes

- Robots: [`src/app/robots.ts`](mdc:src/app/robots.ts)

  - Keep `sitemap` pointing to `${appConfig.app.baseUrl}/sitemap.xml`.

- Sitemap: [`src/app/sitemap.ts`](mdc:src/app/sitemap.ts)

  - Use `appConfig.app.baseUrl` for entries.

- Manifest: [`src/app/manifest.ts`](mdc:src/app/manifest.ts)
  - Derive names, colors, language, and categories from `appConfig`.

### Client/Providers

- `src/app/providers.tsx` is the place to initialize client-only instrumentation; keep it minimal and wrapper-only unless a provider is needed.
